From 925a49deb599f4005a4e315c49852194c68fd051 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rishi <rishi@market-cockpit.local>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 15:25:06 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(ui): light readability + Professional truly distinct +
 earnings still-dark fix
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0076 — three issues from user testing of 0075:

(1) "Light text so so light and cant read"
    Faint gray-blue text colors (#4A5B6C used 171×, #C9D4E0, #8BA3C1,
    #8A95A3, #6B7A8D, #94A3B8, #CBD5E1) all rendered nearly invisible
    on the new white background. Now forced to mid-dark slate #334155.
    Bright text (#F5F7FA, #E6EDF3, #E2E8F0, #FFFFFF) forced to near-
    black #0f172a for headings.

(2) "Dark and Professional same — bad. didnt expected, make it better"
    Professional was visually too close to Dark. Overhauled:
      - Pure #000 page bg (was just dark grey before)
      - All blue accents (#0F7ABF, #06B6D4, #22D3EE, #38A9E8, #3B82F6,
        #38BDF8) → orange/amber (#ffa500)
      - Purple accents (#8B5CF6, #6366F1) → amber yellow (#ffcc00)
      - Panel bg #0a0a0a + border-color rgba(255,165,0,0.30)
      - MONOSPACE FONT applied to every element via * selector
      - Tight letter-spacing 0.01em characteristic of terminals

(3) "Earnings Intelligence still dark in light mode"
    Earnings-analysis page used local BG = '#0a0a0f' constant — that
    hex wasn't in patch 0075's override set. Added:
      #0a0a0f, #0d1117, #0a0f1a, #060a14, #13131a, #2A3B4C, #1A2540,
      #0A1422, #0A1628, #1e293b, #161b22, #1c232c (all variants)
    Plus a SAFETY NET: html[data-theme="light"] main { bg:white } so
    even unmatched inline styles fall through to the main container bg.
    Direct children of main are forced transparent so the safety net
    actually shows.

Files: globals.css only — pure CSS UI patch, no API changes.
---
 frontend/src/app/globals.css | 205 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 166 insertions(+), 39 deletions(-)

diff --git a/frontend/src/app/globals.css b/frontend/src/app/globals.css
index 6f06b12..ece7c75 100644
--- a/frontend/src/app/globals.css
+++ b/frontend/src/app/globals.css
@@ -250,15 +250,13 @@ button[title], a[title] {
 }
 
 /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-   PATCH 0075 — global theme override layer
+   PATCH 0075/0076 — global theme override layer (comprehensive)
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-   The dashboard pages use hardcoded inline-style hex colours (#0A0E1A,
-   #0D1B2E, #1A2840, #F5F7FA, etc.) instead of CSS variables. These don't
-   respond to ThemeContext changes on their own. This layer uses
-   [style*="..."] attribute selectors to override the most common ones when
-   data-theme="light" or "professional" is active.
-   Note: browsers normalize hex inline styles to rgb(R, G, B) at runtime,
-   so we match both forms.
+   Comprehensive override of every common dark hex used in inline styles.
+   The substring matcher [style*="..."] catches them. Both upper and lower
+   case forms must be enumerated (HTML attribute matching IS case-insensitive
+   for the value when using lowercase patterns, but matchings can vary, so
+   we enumerate both for safety).
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
 
 /* Body-level fallback so the page background flips even if no inline style matches */
@@ -280,11 +278,22 @@ html[data-theme="professional"] body {
 }
 
 /* ─── LIGHT THEME OVERRIDES ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
+/* The CSS attribute selector [style*=X] is case-SENSITIVE, so we enumerate
+   uppercase + lowercase forms for every hex. */
 
-/* Page bg #0A0E1A → white */
